          <h1 class="title-xl">Evidence‑informed chiropractic care during pregnancy</h1>
          <p class="muted" style="margin-top:12px; max-width:65ch">Many pregnant people experience back or pelvic pain and other musculoskeletal changes. Chiropractic care may help with comfort, mobility, and function when used safely and collaboratively with your obstetric provider.</p>
          <div class="pill-row" style="margin-top:16px">
            <span class="pill">Patient‑centered</span>
            <span class="pill">Safety first</span>
            <span class="pill">Gentle options</span>
          </div>
          <div style="display:flex; gap:12px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-top:22px">
            <a class="btn primary" href="#benefits">Explore Benefits</a>
            <a class="btn ghost" href="#evidence">View the Evidence</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="p">
              <div class="grid" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:16px">
                <div style="grid-column:1/-1">
                  <img class="avatar-img" alt="Pregnant person receiving gentle side‑lying chiropractic care" src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1603912816541-1d0f7d3c06d0?q=80&w=1200&auto=format&fit=crop" />
                </div>
                <div>
                  <div class="kicker">Common symptoms</div>
                  <ul class="muted list">
                    <li>Low back or pelvic girdle pain</li>
                    <li>Sciatica‑like leg pain</li>
                    <li>Mid‑back/rib discomfort</li>
                    <li>Postural strain and stiffness</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <div class="kicker">Care goals</div>
                  <ul class="muted list">
                    <li>Reduce pain and tension</li>
                    <li>Improve mobility and daily function</li>
                    <li>Support better sleep and activity</li>
                    <li>Prepare for the physical demands of birth</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
